CloudMediaContext
AzureAdTokenCredentials
AzureAdTokenProvider
IAsset
IJob
IMediaProcessor
etc. 

Making these examples out of date and useless. When attempting to use the old windowsazure.mediaservices package in my function.proj. I get the following error when my function attempts to download the nuget packages (I'm using azure console for this).
error NU1101: Unable to find package windowsazure.mediaservice. No packages exist with this id in source(s): nuget.org

Can you place update the documentation and this project accordingly? 'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': '## Description
My caption data is properly embedded with fragmented MP4. I did not know that videos would automatically read the manifest information and show captions. I hadn't seen it work an entire day. I came to work and there they were. I realized that if I refresh a video after ~3 minutes, it won't work. I think it has to do with the way it tries to download all the fragments from the manifest on reload.

## Steps to reproduce
Explain in detail the exact steps necessary to reproduce the issue.
1. Open a browser window with player. 
2. Start streaming valid IMSC1 caption data
3. See captions come in
4. Watch for ~3 minutes
5. Open new browser window
6. See that captions aren't showing in new window
7. See that captions are still showing on old window

## Results
### Expected
The captions did not show up.

### Actual
The captions should show

### Error output
None

## Additional Information
Please include any additional information necessary here. Including the following:
### versions
#### videojs
what version of videojs does this occur with? 7.6.5
#### browsers
what browser are affected? tested latest chrome & firefox
#### OSes
what platforms (operating systems and devices) are affected? on mac currently
### plugins
are any videojs plugins being used on the page? If so, please list them below.
```
    "videojs-contrib-quality-levels": "^2.0.9",
    "videojs-dvr": "^1.4.0",
    "videojs-errors": "^4.3.0",
    "videojs-hls-quality-selector": "^1.1.0"
```', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/videojs/video.js/issues/6353/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/videojs/video.js/issues/6353/timeline', 'performed_via_github_app': None}, 'comment': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/videojs/video.js/issues/comments/1055990359', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/videojs/video.js/issues/6353#issuecomment-1055990359', 'issue_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/videojs/video.js/issues/6353', 'id': 1055990359, 'node_id': 'IC_kwDOAAotfs4-8SJX', 'user': {'login': 'johndeu', 'id': 39712, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjM5NzEy', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39712?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/johndeu', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/johndeu/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, 'created_at': '2022-03-02T00:02:11Z', 'updated_at': '2022-03-02T00:02:11Z', 'author_association': 'NONE', 'body': 'Not sure why this Issue is marked as closed. The preview URL should work just fine for HLS or DASH, and works like the live output streams (just without archiving to disk or DVR playback support).  You can add usual format tags to the manifest URL to get various output formats.

The video component is based on [Plyr](https://github.com/sampotts/plyr) and supports:

- `Source` parameter can accept `string` and complex object(VideoSource)
- HLS and DASH streaming videos. Requires explicitly defining it with `StreamingLibrary` parameter
